Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, pop a #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Add the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Harissa Paste{50%g}, @Dried Oregano{1%sachet}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{50%ml}.

Stir to combine and bring to the boil. Simmer, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Parma Ham & Parmigiano Reggiano Filled Pasta{250%g}, ~{3%minutes}.

Drain and drizzle with @oil{}.

Next, halve the @Ciabatta{1}.

Toast the ciabatta halves in your #toaster{} until golden. Drizzle with oil and season with @salt{}.

Add the @Butter{30%g} and @Baby Spinach{40%g} to the sauce in handfuls, making sure it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the cooked pasta.

Share the pasta between your #bowls{}.

Crumble over the @Greek Style Salad Cheese{50%g}.

Serve the ciabatta alongside.

Enjoy!

